3. Use Row Widget in Flutter App Development

✅ Explanation (Exam-Oriented)

The Row widget in Flutter is used to arrange multiple widgets horizontally (in a single line).
It is useful when you want elements side by side like buttons, text, or icons.

Key properties:

mainAxisAlignment → controls horizontal spacing
crossAxisAlignment → controls vertical alignment 

//main code


import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(MyApp());
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: RowExample(),
    );
  }
}

class RowExample extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      appBar: AppBar(
        title: Text("Row Widget Example"),
      ),
      body: Row(
        mainAxisAlignment: MainAxisAlignment.spaceEvenly,
        children: [
          Icon(Icons.star, size: 40, color: Colors.red),
          Icon(Icons.star, size: 40, color: Colors.green),
          Icon(Icons.star, size: 40, color: Colors.blue),
        ],
      ),
    );
  }
}